      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    rajño <persName key="pers:VpŚrīSātakarṇi">vāsithīputasa 
	      siri sādakanisa</persName> 
	    <date when-custom="5"
		  datingPoint="pers:VpŚrīSātakarṇi"
		  datingMethod="regnal">savachare 5</date>
	    gīmhāna pakhe 4 divasa 5 utarāhakona sātavāhana samaṇena
	    ujukā pato catārica pāyako deya dhama
	  <lb n="2"/>
	    sava budhapucāya mātāpitūna punyāya 
	    sava<lb n="3" break="no"/>lokahi<supplied reason="lost">ta</supplied>sughāya
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  On the fifth day of the fourth (fortnight) of the summer, in the
	  fifth year of the reign of King
	  <persName key="pers:VpŚrīSātakarṇi">Vāsiṣṭīputra Śrī
	  Sātakarṇi</persName>, meritorious gift of medhi slab,
	  umbrella, and uprights were made by Sātavāhana Śramaṇa of
	  Uttarāhakona, for the workship of all the Buddhas, towards the
	  merit of (his) parents and the well-being of all the worlds.
	</p>
      </div>
